1.8.name: wordpress/vr-visitas
1.8.description:
This plugin allows you to keep track of visits to your page.

You can display the counter of visits and other data on your pages, and you can filter the results by controlling the time, IP and visits you consider trash.

To get data from users, this plugin uses:

  • If the function get_browser() is not active in your server, uses a call to user defined function get_browser_local() developed by Alexandre Alapetite that uses a local browscap.ini included as a library with this plugin. You can get an updated version of this library in: browscap.ini.
  • To display Country stats, you need to install the ip2nation data on your database, if not installed the report for Country stats remain inactive. Yo can download the mySql data from ip2nation.<
